article.description: Chaisson Allen, a preseason All-Colonial Athletic Association pick, scored 20 points and Northeastern held on to beat Boston U. 66-64 on Friday night in the season opener for both teams.
article.headline: Chaisson Allen scores 20 to help Northeastern hold off BU
article.linkText: Allen scores 20 to help Northeastern hold off BU
article.story: BOSTON -- Chaisson Allen, a preseason All-Colonial Athletic Association pick, scored 20 points and Northeastern held on to beat Boston U. 66-64 on Friday night in the season opener for both teams. Three other Huskies scored in double figures -- freshman Alex Harris had 12 points, Kauri Black had 11 points and 12 rebounds, and Joel Smith added 10 points. The win snapped a two-game losing streak in the series for Northeastern and gave the Huskies their third straight win in home openers. Northeastern led by 13 at halftime but the Terriers chipped away and cut the lead to 58-57 with 3:41 to play after a 14-2 run. The Huskies answered with a 6-2 run for a 64-59 lead with 1:24 to play, and iced the game on two free throws by Harris for a 66-62 lead with 4 seconds remaining. John Holland led the Terriers with 25 points and D.J. Irving added 14. Irving
